2011-12-12  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmIconMan/MvwmIconMan.1.in:
	Mention "Transient" option to MvwmIconMan can now only be specified as
	"-Transient".

2011-11-26  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.c (ButtonPressProcess):
	Remove calls to XDestroyWindow for -transient buttons

	Rather than forcibly destroying the window which has been swallowed when
	closing MvwmButtons from a -transient option, instead let the atexit()
	routine handle this for us, which also correctly handles Swallowed
	state, etc.  Noticed by David Fries.

2011-11-07  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmButtons/ConfigMvwmButtons:
	Remove delay to panelised MvwmPager

	Caused too many confusions.

2011-10-15  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmRearrange/MvwmRearrange.c (parse_args,
	move_resize_raise_window):
	Make MvwmRearrange understand Move's "ewmhiwa" option when calculating
	where to place its windows.

2011-09-18  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmIconMan/MvwmIconMan.c (main):
	Remove unnecessary strncasecmp()

2011-08-27  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.c (DeadPipeCleanup):
	Add XSync() call back.

	This won't hurt, and for broken applications, will make them work again.
	When will a WM *stop* being a means to circumvent bugs in applications?

2011-08-21  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* modules/MvwmScript/Instructions.c (FuncGetOutput):
	Fix reading of output via GetOutput.

2011-08-06  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
    * modules/MvwmAnimate/MvwmAnimate.c (main, Loop):
    * modules/MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.c (RedrawWindow):
    * modules/MvwmButtons/draw.c (RedrawButton):
    * modules/MvwmCpp/MvwmCpp.c (cpp_defs):
    * modules/MvwmForm/MvwmForm.c (OpenWindows):
    * modules/MvwmForm/ParseCommand.c (ParseCommand):
