                                         ExecuteAction):
    * modules/MvwmIconMan/readconfig.c (handle_button_config):
    * modules/MvwmM4/MvwmM4.c (m4_defs):
    * modules/MvwmPager/MvwmPager.c (list_icon_name):
    * modules/MvwmPager/x_pager.c (PictureIconWindow,
                                   IconMoveWindow):
    * modules/MvwmProxy/MvwmProxy.c (parse_options,
                                     send_command_to_mvwm,
                                     GetProperty, GetLeader,
                                     GetParentProcessId):
    * modules/MvwmRearrange/MvwmRearrange.c (main):
    * modules/MvwmScript/MvwmScript.c (ReadMvwmScriptArg):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Instructions.c (InfEq, Sup, IfThen,
                                         FuncGetOutput):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Widgets/HScrollBar.c (EvtMouseHScrollBar):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Widgets/Menu.c (EvtMouseMenu):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Widgets/PopupMenu.c (EvtMousePopupMenu):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Widgets/PushButton.c (EvtMousePushButton):
    * modules/MvwmScript/Widgets/RadioButton.c (EvtMouseRadioButton):
    * modules/MvwmTaskBar/MvwmTaskBar.c (HandleEvents):
    * modules/MvwmWharf/MvwmWharf.c (Loop, CreateVizWindow,
                                     CreateWindow, ParseOptions):
    * modules/MvwmWinList/ButtonArray.c (DoButton):
    * modules/MvwmWinList/MvwmWinList.c (StartMeUp_I):
	Fix -Wset-but-not-used-variable warnings

	This removes dead declarations in code which were never used.  This is
	the default in GCC 4.6, and whilst we could turn this feature off with
	-Wno-set-but-not-used-variable, it's a good chance to clean this up.

2011-06-06  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.c (DeadPipeCleanup):
	Don't grab the XServer when exiting MvwmButtons

	When MvwmButtons is asked to quit and the _atexit() handler is run, do
	not grab the xserver when cleaning up, as there's every chance it might
	still be grabbed when MVWM goes to reinstall its pixmaps, leading to an
	infinite loop.

2011-04-15  Thomas Adam <thomas@mvwm.org>
	* MvwmIconMan/xmanager.c (draw_empty_manager):
	Compile warnings fix.

2010-12-26    <despen@verizon.net>

	* MvwmForm/Makefile.am: Add file MvwmForm-Desktop.

	* MvwmForm/MvwmForm-Desktop: New form, MvwmForm-Desktop.

2010-10-15  Thomas Adam <thomas@xteddy.org>
	* MvwmIconMan/MvwmIconMan.c (main):
	Allow Transient mode to accept explicit module alias.

	When running MvwmIconMan in transient mode, allow for an explicit module
	alias to be used, rather than defaulting to "MvwmIconMan".  This brings
	MvwmIconMan in-line with other modules which provide similar
	functionality.

2010-08-16  Thomas Adam  <thomas@xteddy.org>
	* MvwmTasBar/MvwmTaskBar.c (ProcessMessage):
	Use the correct border hints to calculate screen width.

	When calculating the size of the MvwmTaskBar, ensure we get the
	information from the newer border size hints, and don't use the old one.
	This fixes an incredibly long-standing bug in MvwmTaskBar.  I hope I win
	a prize.  :)

2010-08-06  Chris Siebenmann <cks-mvwm@cs.toronto.edu>
	* MvwmIconMan/mvwm.c (count_nonsticky_in_hashtable):
	Correctly handle iconified windows with sticky icons.

	When counting how many windows we expect configure window messages
	for after changing to a new page, don't count iconified windows
	with sticky icons (ones styled with StickyIcon or any of its
	variants).


2009-12-19  Thomas Adam <thomas.adam22@gmail.com>
	* MvwmForm/MvwmForm.c (MainLoop):
	Stop relying on XSync() after FD_SET when using FPending() will
	automatically return correctly for handling queued events.  This cures
	the problem of the window appearing not to have drawn all its widgets
	properly when it is initially mapped.

