	(ParseButton):
	(ParsePanel):
	* MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.h:
	Added a (no)MvwmModule flags to Swallow

	* MvwmButtons/MvwmButtons.c (main):
	(process_message):
	(handle_config_info_packet):
	(change_colorset):
	(DeadPipeCleanup):
	(recursive_change_colorset):
	(swallow):
	(send_bg_change_to_module):
	* MvwmButtons/draw.c (RedrawButton):
	* MvwmBacker/MvwmBacker.c (ProcessMessage):
	* MvwmDragWell/mvwmDragWell.c (myXNextEvent):
	* MvwmWinList/MvwmWinList.c (ProcessMessage):
	(main):
	* MvwmTaskBar/MvwmTaskBar.c (main):
	(ProcessMessage):
	* MvwmScript/MvwmScript.c (main):
	(MainLoop):
	MvwmScript/types.h:
	* MvwmIdent/MvwmIdent.c (list_end):
	(main):
	(list_property_change):
	MvwmIdent/MvwmIdent.h:
	* MvwmIconMan/MvwmIconMan.h:
	* MvwmIconMan/mvwm.c (property_change):
	(handle_config_info):
	* MvwmPager/MvwmPager.c (list_property_change):
	(process_message):
	(main):
	* MvwmPager/MvwmPager.h:
	* MvwmIconBox/MvwmIconBox.c (process_message):
	(Loop):
	* MvwmForm/MvwmForm.c (main):
	(process_message):
	(ParseActiveMessage):
	MvwmButtons and mvwm2 can send a MX_PROPERTY_CHANGE message with
	MX_PROPERTY_CHANGE_BACKGROUND and a window id as argument to modules.
	Then, the modules update their background if needed.
	MvwmButtons sends a MX_PROPERTY_CHANGE message with
	MX_PROPERTY_CHANGE_SWALLOW and the id the modules when it
	swallow a mvwm module. Swallowable modules handle this message.
	Removed the ROOT_BG_CHANGE_STRING stuff.

